cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a methodology to analyze and interpret decisions from neural models in natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the trade-off between neural networks' success and interpretability, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions using reinforcement learning, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper analyzes multiple NLP tasks, including sentiment analysis, which could suggest it belongs to cs.CV (Computer Vision) due to the use of natural language processing techniques in computer vision tasks.
